linux mint hardening guide
linux firejail

https://easylinuxtipsproject.blogspot.com/p/sandbox.html
sudo apt-get install firejail
firejail firefox

create a desktop shortcut that launches Firefox in a sandbox by default.
a right-click with your mouse on the icon of Firefox in the menu - Add to desktop. Then right-click on the newly created desktop shortcut - Properties - Command: change this into:
firejail firefox %u

firejail --tree

Press Enter.

With that command you can check whether Firefox is indeed running in sandbox mode.



firejail google-chrome-stable

